sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K809308
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The RFP is linked with signal peptide of Zim17, GAL promoter and ADH1 terminator. When expressed in cytoplasm, it will be located into mitochondrial matrix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: All parts should be correctly linked without frame shift

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K809301
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RFY is linked with signal peptide of ZIM17, thus can be directed into mitochondrial matrix. It is used to test and signal peptide.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part BBa_K809201 and BBa_E1010 should be correctly linked without frame shift

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: SPzim17
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: this part is the sequence of transit signal peptide of ZIM17. It can help protein target to the mitochondrial matrix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Luohao Xu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Zim17, a novel zinc finger protein essential for protein import into mitochondria. J Biol Chem. 2004 Nov 26 ;279(48):50243-9. Epub 2004 Sep 21 . http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P42844
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: it is synthesized based on the complete sequence of signal peptide of ZIM17

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.
